The CCS score for all exons and genes was calculated with the ExomeCQA program. The CCS score provides a measure of percentage of base pairs in a given region for which coverage is less than 10 reads in multiple samples (see Figure S9). The CCS score is calculated by the formula:1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
